highlights.description: Asks participants to share a personal story to help others understand them.
Augustine's story prompts Rachel to change her thinking about the consequence of these empty houses.
Imagining the experience of people in other boroughs/neighborhoods.
Maura expresses pleasure at having met a person who purchased an apartment building and turned it into a single family home as it humanized him.  But still disagrees with the practice on the whole.

title: Hudson Park Library Launch Conversation - Community Changes in Greenwich Village
